SIMPLE: underhanded
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Underhanded
<hw>Un"der*hand`ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Underhand;
clandestine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1570 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Insufficiently provided with hands or workers;
short-handed; sparsely populated; <mark>obsolete</mark> in this sense,
<altname>short-handed</altname> or <altname>understaffed</altname> being
the preferrred term.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+JG</source>]</p>

<p><q>Norway . . . might defy the world, . . . but it is much
<qex>underhanded</qex> now.</q> <rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underhandedly</ent>⟦br⟧
